<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="town-n">town <strong><em>n</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /taʊn/    美 /taʊn/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>镇；城镇；(与农村相对的) 城市：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>A town is usually smaller than a city but larger than a village. 
镇通常比城市小，但比村庄大。</p></div>

<h4 id="2">2.★ <strong>(某一市镇的) 居民；市民：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I suppose the whole town is talking about it. 
我想全城的人都在议论这件事。</p></div>

<h4 id="3">3.★ <strong>商业中心区：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>He had to go up to town that morning on business.
那天早上他得去市中心办公事。</p></div></div>